snippet.title: 1st T20I | Highlights | New Zealand Tour Of Sri Lanka | 9th November 2024
snippet.description:
Sri Lanka and New Zealand faced each other in the 1st T20I at the Rangiri Dambulla International Stadium. New Zealand batted first and posted 135 runs before getting all out in 19.3 overs. Later, Sri Lanka faced some trouble during the chase but managed to get over the line in the end as they won by 4 wickets.

Follow the journey of two individuals brought together by family, tradition, and culture, who slowly discover friendship, trust, and eventually, love. Watch how their worlds collide and connect as they navigate new experiences, overcome misunderstandings, and learn what it means to truly love and respect each other.

Each episode of Arranged Marriage delves into the beauty of growing affection and genuine connection, showcasing how relationships can blossom in surprising ways. If you enjoy stories of romance, personal growth, and cultural dynamics, subscribe and hit the notification bell for every chapter of this emotional and heartwarming series.

Dr. Hathi is back to the Gokuldham Society after a break. He makes a heroic entry in a rented car, eating bananas. Everyone is happy to meet him after a long time.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

Maayavi Minugu Neenu 
Munjaane Bisilu Neenu 

Saaladhiro Haadu Neenu
Bekeniso Sanje Neenu 
 
Edheya Dhunige 
Belaku Neene
Neenaadhe Neenaadhe 

Yaariradha Rastheyalli
Santhaiso Avale Gaali  
Saagaradha Baaninalli 
Kangoliso Avale Neeli 

Samayaa Nee Ninthodhe
Avala Angayyalle 
Nanoonu Sharanaadhe 
Avala Gunginalle 

Sothe Hodhe Sothe Hodhe 

Nee Modhala Koneyaa Aase 
Nanna Edhege Hidiso Bhaashe

Anuraagadhali Konebeedhiyali 
Nanagu Ninagu Mane Maadiruve 
Olage Baralu Thada Inneke 
Kitakeele Naa Kaadhe 

Yaaro Naa Yaro Kanasalli Yaaru Iradhaga 
Nannavala Manasalli Naanage Bekitthu Jaaga
Ee Hrudhaya Mouna Aaguvaaaga 
Maathu Hege Aadali 

Huduki Hodhe Ello Dhooori 
Nine Sikka Shaayari

Sothe Hodhe Sothe Hodhe 

Nee Modhala Koneyaa Aase 
Nanna Edhege Hidiso Bhaashe

In this video, Roshan Anand Sir shares the story of his struggles and the beginning of his journey toward preparing for an engineering career. He explains how he had to seek help from relatives just to reach Patna and openly talks about the pain of feeling unable to fulfill his parents‚Äô dreams, along with the uncertainty he faced regarding his future, where he saw two paths: preparing for a government job or teaching in coaching.

The years 2014 to 2016 were critical for him, as he faced numerous personal challenges, including his grandfather‚Äôs battle with cancer and severe financial difficulties, which hindered his grandfather‚Äôs access to proper treatment. The period from 2013 to 2017 marked a significant economic crisis for him. To support himself, Roshan Sir began offering home tuition in his village, where, in exchange for teaching, he received meals and lodging from other village residents. Many of his students went on to achieve success, a testament to his dedication.

During the COVID-19 pandemic, Roshan Anand Sir‚Äôs passion for helping students led him to conduct outdoor classes on the banks of the Ganges, where he faced various administrative restrictions. His coaching institute, "Gyan Bindu GS Patna," helped over 1,000 students secure positions as constables in the Bihar Police force. Roshan Sir himself passed the written exam four times but could not clear the physical tests.

In this video, Roshan Anand Sir shares the story of his struggles and the beginning of his journey toward preparing for an engineering career. He explains how he had to seek help from relatives just to reach Patna and openly talks about the pain of feeling unable to fulfill his parents‚Äô dreams, along with the uncertainty he faced regarding his future, where he saw two paths: preparing for a government job or teaching in coaching.

The years 2014 to 2016 were critical for him, as he faced numerous personal challenges, including his grandfather‚Äôs battle with cancer and severe financial difficulties, which hindered his grandfather‚Äôs access to proper treatment. The period from 2013 to 2017 marked a significant economic crisis for him. To support himself, Roshan Sir began offering home tuition in his village, where, in exchange for teaching, he received meals and lodging from other village residents. Many of his students went on to achieve success, a testament to his dedication.

During the COVID-19 pandemic, Roshan Anand Sir‚Äôs passion for helping students led him to conduct outdoor classes on the banks of the Ganges, where he faced various administrative restrictions. His coaching institute, "Gyan Bindu GS Patna," helped over 1,000 students secure positions as constables in the Bihar Police force. Roshan Sir himself passed the written exam four times but could not clear the physical tests.

snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi

snippet.description:

‚≠êÔ∏èJoin our Storytelling MasterClass for Youtube : https://monkeymagic.wtf/

Devenko :  https://www.instagram.com/devenko26/
Monkey Magic : https://www.instagram.com/monkeyxmagic/
BigBroBaljeet :  https://www.instagram.com/bigbrobaljeet/

===========================================================
üìß Email üìß : monkeymagic@create.wtf 
===========================================================

In this video we do a roadtrip starting from New Delhi driving all the way to Demchok, LAC. We spend some two nights in Hanle, mesmerised by the stargazing experience, went to Umingla - which is world's highest motorable pass! 

About My Hilux (Baljeet) 
After almost a decade of waiting I finally have this, this what you see here is my love, is the sole reason I have worked so hard over the last years. I have had this impossible dream of driving from New Delhi to London since 2012-2014 now, but when I see 2014 I see this as an important dream. Our first car in 2013 was a second hand Maruti Suzuki Alto and to be able to reach here today has been a lot of sweat, sleepless nights and prayers!

But you see, today I'm here and this is just the start of my impossible dream. To be able to go anywhere, live anywhere. To be free on the road & off road.. I shall have my freedom and this beast that you see here today is just what will give me my freedom.

Everyone, meet Baljeet, that is going to take me & you to lots and lots of far off places. Let the adventure begin!

===========================================================

In this video we do a roadtrip starting from New Delhi driving all the way to Demchok, LAC. We spend some two nights in Hanle, mesmerised by the stargazing experience, went to Umingla - which is world's highest motorable pass! 

About My Hilux (Baljeet) 
After almost a decade of waiting I finally have this, this what you see here is my love, is the sole reason I have worked so hard over the last years. I have had this impossible dream of driving from New Delhi to London since 2012-2014 now, but when I see 2014 I see this as an important dream. Our first car in 2013 was a second hand Maruti Suzuki Alto and to be able to reach here today has been a lot of sweat, sleepless nights and prayers!

But you see, today I'm here and this is just the start of my impossible dream. To be able to go anywhere, live anywhere. To be free on the road & off road.. I shall have my freedom and this beast that you see here today is just what will give me my freedom.

Everyone, meet Baljeet, that is going to take me & you to lots and lots of far off places. Let the adventure begin!

snippet.description:

#secretagent #vijayantony #mazhaipidikkathamanithan

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS Sporting CP 4-1 Man City | Foden, Gyorkeres hat-trick & Araujo goals
snippet.description:
City suffered a night of Champions League disappointment, losing out 4-1 at Sporting CP with Viktor Gyokeres hitting a hat-trick for the hosts.

Pep Guardiola‚Äôs side had got off to a flying start in Lisbon going ahead thanks to a fourth minute goal from Phil Foden.

The Blues ‚Äì who handed teenage defender Jahmai Simpson-Pusey a full debut ‚Äì dominated the first half carving out a host of other chances.

But, out of nowhere, Gyokeres struck to level affairs late in the first half before Sporting then scored twice within three minutes at the start of the second half through Maximiliano Araujo and Gyokeres, via a penalty, to seize control.

snippet.title: Sharda Sinha Death: 'Bihar Kokila' Synonymous With Chhath Songs Passes Away During Festival At 72
snippet.description:
Sharda Sinha Death: 'Bihar Kokila' Synonymous With Chhath Songs Passes Away During Festival At 72

Renowned Bihari singer Sharda Sinha, known as the 'Bihar Kokila,' passes away at 72. Sinha was in critical condition on ventilator support after her hospitalization. Her health declined shortly after the death of her husband, Brajkishore Sinha, in September. Sharda's son Anshuman confirms her passing, mourning both a beloved mother and an iconic artist. Known for traditional wedding and Chhath songs in Bhojpuri, Sinha made a lasting impact on the music scene. Her music celebrated cultural festivals, making her a cherished figure in the industry.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

snippet.title: Skoda Kylaq - The Perfect Skoda for India | First Look
snippet.description: The much anticipated Skoda Kylaq - the sub-4 metre compact SUV - finally made its debut in India today. Interestingly the company also revealed the introductory price of its base trim. It‚Äôs priced at Rs 7.89 lacs (ex-showroom), thus making it the most affordable car from the brand. Based on the same MQB A0-IN platform, the Kushaq features the same 1.0L TSI (113bhp, 178Nm) that also powers the Slavia and Kushaq. Much like its siblings, this too will be made available with both 6-speed AT and 6-speed MT. To offer better ride quality, Skoda has also reworked on its suspension compared to the Kushaq. It‚Äôs 3995mm in length, and has a wheelbase of 2556mm and ground clearance of 189mm.
